    "id": "samarkand",
    "name": {
      "en": "Samarkand",
      "uz": "Samarqand"
    },
    "lat": 39.627,
    "lon": 66.975,
    "article": [
      "Samarkand is one of the oldest cities in the world and a jewel of the Silk Road. For over two thousand years caravans, scholars and conquerors have passed through it.",
      "Its turquoise domes and the vast Registan square have drawn travellers for centuries. Timur made the city the capital of his empire, and his grandson Ulugʻbek built a famous observatory here to map the stars."
    ],
