  {
    "id": "bukhara",
    "name": {
      "en": "Bukhara",
      "uz": "Buxoro"
    },
    "lat": 39.767,
    "lon": 64.421,
    "article": [
      "Bukhara is a living museum of mosques, madrasahs and minarets, little changed in centuries. Its old centre is one of the best-preserved medieval towns in Central Asia.",
      "The towering Kalon minaret once guided caravans across the desert and is so beautiful that, it is said, even Genghis Khan spared it. Around the Lyabi-Hauz pool, traders still sell carpets and gold embroidery."
    ],
