  {
    "id": "khiva",
    "name": {
      "en": "Khiva",
      "uz": "Xiva"
    },
    "lat": 41.378,
    "lon": 60.364,
    "article": [
      "Khiva's old town, Ichan-Qalʼa, sits behind tall mud-brick walls like a city from a fairy tale. Step through the gates and you walk among carved wooden columns and blue-tiled minarets.",
      "For travellers crossing the Kyzylkum desert, Khiva was the last great oasis before the long road west — and, less proudly, a notorious slave market. Today its narrow lanes are quiet and beautifully restored."
    ],
