  {
    "id": "tashkent",
    "name": {
      "en": "Tashkent",
      "uz": "Toshkent"
    },
    "lat": 41.311,
    "lon": 69.28,
    "article": [
      "Tashkent, the capital, is Central Asia's largest city and a busy mix of old and new. A powerful earthquake in 1966 reshaped much of it, leaving wide avenues, leafy parks and a grand, mosaic-lined metro.",
      "At the sprawling Chorsu bazaar, under its great blue dome, you can still buy bread, spices and fruit much as people have for generations. Quiet old mahallas survive between the modern boulevards."
