    "id": "fergana",
    "name": {
      "en": "Fergana Valley",
      "uz": "Fargʻona vodiysi"
    },
    "lat": 40.389,
    "lon": 71.783,
    "article": [
      "The Fergana Valley is the green, fertile heart of Uzbekistan, ringed by mountains and watered by the Syr Darya. Cotton, fruit and mulberry trees fill its fields.",
      "Its towns are famous for crafts: bright atlas silk woven in Margʻilon, glazed ceramics from Rishton and the curved knives of Chust. In late summer the markets overflow with apricots, melons and grapes."
    ],
