  {
    "id": "aral",
    "name": {
      "en": "Aral Sea & Nukus",
      "uz": "Orol dengizi"
    },
    "lat": 43.766,
    "lon": 59.02,
    "article": [
      "The Aral Sea was once one of the largest lakes on Earth, but it has nearly dried away after its rivers were diverted to irrigate cotton — a stark lesson in how quickly people can change a landscape.",
      "Near Moʻynoq, rusting fishing ships now rest on bare sand where waves once broke. In nearby Nukus, the Savitsky Museum guards a remarkable collection of avant-garde art once forbidden by the Soviet state."
    ],
